description:
The Tadpole Nebula is an emission nebula in the constellation Auriga. The Tadpoles proper are rich in hydrogen and sulphur emissions and stand out against a background of mostly oxygen signal. 

To create the starless version for processing of the narrowband data, I used the code Starnet by Nikita Misiura, folowed by clean-up in Photoshop CC. Reference: https://www.astrobin.com/339099/

Version A: Wide crop of the IC410 nebula region
Version B:  Tight crop of the Tadpoles
Version C: Starless image of IC410
Version G: No tone mapping. I decided to reprocess the data and was a more natural palette of colors starting from cross-blended SHO.

All data acquired with ZWO ASI1600MM Pro, Gain=139, Offset=50. 75% of acquired data was retained for processing (discarded subs were eliminated due to bad seeing or wind).
title: The Tadpole Nebula (IC410)
